# Pipes

*dplyr* provides a handy *pipe* operator to chain the results of functions into other functions. In Data Engineering and Data Science, this is particularly useful when applying multiple transformations to a data object:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
suppressPackageStartupMessages({
  library(dplyr)
  library(gt)
})


iris %>% 
  group_by(Species) %>% 
  summarise(sepal_length = mean(Sepal.Length),
            speal_width = mean(Sepal.Width)) %>% 
  gt() %>% 
  tab_header(
    title = "Mean Sepal Length and Width for Iris Dataset"
  )
```

